## Two-layer system

This project uses Tailwind CSS v4 and MUI v9 together:

- **Tailwind** — layout, spacing, typography, colour, responsive breakpoints.
- **MUI** — interactive components with built-in accessibility: `Button`, `TextField`, `Select`, `Dialog`, `Snackbar`, `CircularProgress`, etc.

Use the right tool for the job. Do not rebuild MUI primitives from scratch with Tailwind, and do not fight MUI's structure with deep Tailwind overrides.

## App theme (required on every new feature)

All new pages and components must use the shared theme — never introduce ad-hoc colours or one-off layout shells.

**Source of truth:** `src/lib/theme/tokens.ts`

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `background` | `#FAF3DD` | Page backgrounds |
| `primary` | `#053B06` | Headings, primary actions, primary text |
| `secondary` | `#6E9075` | Supporting copy, secondary actions |

**Supporting files:**

- `src/lib/theme/muiTheme.ts` — MUI `createTheme` (palette, typography, component overrides)
- `src/lib/theme/AppThemeProvider.tsx` — wraps the app; already mounted in `main.tsx`
- `src/index.css` — Tailwind `@theme inline` maps semantic utilities to CSS vars (`--mp-*`)

**Adding or changing colours:**

1. Update `brandColors` / `semanticColors` / `brandAlpha` in `tokens.ts`
2. Mirror new CSS vars in `cssVariableDefinitions` and `@theme inline` in `index.css`
3. Extend `muiTheme.ts` if MUI palette slots need updating

**Consuming colours:**

- **MUI components** — `color="primary"`, `color="secondary"`, or `sx` with theme tokens (`color: 'text.secondary'`, `bgcolor: 'background.paper'`)
- **Non-MUI elements** — Tailwind semantic utilities: `bg-background`, `text-primary`, `text-secondary`, `border-border`, `bg-primary-subtle`
- **Transparency** — use `brandAlpha` or `brandColorWithAlpha()` from `tokens.ts`; do not hand-roll `rgba(...)`

```tsx
// Correct — theme tokens
<p className="text-sm text-secondary">Supporting copy</p>
<Button variant="contained" color="primary">Save</Button>

// Wrong — hardcoded or generic palette colours
<p className="text-sm text-gray-600">Supporting copy</p>
<Button sx={{ bgcolor: '#053B06' }}>Save</Button>
```

Do not hardcode hex values in pages or components. Do not use generic Tailwind palette classes (`text-slate-700`, `bg-blue-600`, etc.) when a semantic token exists.

## PageHarness (required for standalone card pages)

For centered, card-based pages (auth, onboarding, password reset, and similar standalone flows), use **`PageHarness`** from `src/components/layout/PageHarness.tsx`. Do not hand-roll `<main>` + `Paper` layouts.

**Canonical examples:** `LoginPage`, `RegisterPage`

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `PageHarness` | Root wrapper — full-viewport background + centered card (`maxWidth`: `sm` \| `md` \| `lg`) |
| `PageHarnessHeader` | Title + optional description |
| `PageHarnessForm` | Form with standard field spacing (`gap-5`) |
| `PageHarnessFooter` | Centered footer copy |
| `PageHarnessLink` | Themed react-router link |

```tsx
// Correct — new standalone card page
import {
  PageHarness,
  PageHarnessFooter,
  PageHarnessForm,
  PageHarnessHeader,
  PageHarnessLink,
} from '../components/layout/PageHarness';

export default function ResetPasswordPage() {
  return (
    <PageHarness>
      <PageHarnessHeader title="Reset password" description="We'll email you a link." />
      <PageHarnessForm onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
        <TextField label="Email" fullWidth />
        <Button type="submit" variant="contained" color="primary" size="large" fullWidth>
          Send link
        </Button>
      </PageHarnessForm>
      <PageHarnessFooter>
        <PageHarnessLink to="/login">Back to sign in</PageHarnessLink>
      </PageHarnessFooter>
    </PageHarness>
  );
}

// Wrong — bespoke layout duplicating the harness
<main className="flex min-h-screen items-center justify-center bg-[#FAF3DD]">
  <Paper className="p-8">...</Paper>
</main>
```

**Inside the harness:**

- Use MUI `TextField` / `Button` with `fullWidth`, `size="large"`, and `color="primary"` or `color="secondary"`
- Place optional secondary actions (e.g. OAuth buttons) as siblings between `PageHarnessForm` and `PageHarnessFooter`
- Do not re-style the card, header, or footer — extend the harness components if the design system needs new slots

**Authenticated app pages** (lists, detail views, dashboards) do not use `PageHarness`. They still must use theme tokens for all colour and typography. When an app-level shell exists (`AppShell` or similar), use that instead of inventing a new page wrapper.

## Tailwind

- Apply Tailwind classes directly on JSX elements for layout and spacing.
- Use Tailwind for `flex`, `grid`, `gap`, `p-*`, `m-*`, `text-*`, `font-*`, `rounded-*`, `border`, `shadow`.
- Use responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) for breakpoints — do not write media queries manually.
- Prefer semantic colour utilities (`text-primary`, `bg-background`) over generic palette names.
- Do not use arbitrary values (`w-[347px]`, `bg-[#FAF3DD]`) unless a design token genuinely doesn't exist.

```tsx
// Correct — Tailwind for layout, semantic colours
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 p-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <RecipeCard recipe={recipe} />
</div>

// Wrong — inline styles for layout
<div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '16px' }}>
```

## MUI components

- Import MUI components from `@mui/material`.
- Use the `size` and `variant` props instead of overriding dimensions manually.
- For minor visual tweaks on MUI components, prefer the `sx` prop with theme tokens over adding a Tailwind class on the MUI component root.
- Do not wrap a MUI `Button` in a `<div>` just to add spacing — use Tailwind on the surrounding container or harness slots.

```tsx
// Correct
<Button variant="contained" color="primary" size="large" fullWidth>
  Save recipe
</Button>

// Wrong — reimplementing what MUI already provides
<button className="bg-green-900 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Save recipe</button>
```

## MUI + Tailwind conflict avoidance

- MUI renders with Emotion; Tailwind injects via the Vite plugin. Specificity conflicts are rare but can occur.
- If a Tailwind class on a MUI component root has no effect, use `sx` with theme tokens instead.
- Do not apply MUI `sx` for layout concerns that Tailwind handles — keep concerns separated.

```tsx
// Correct — Tailwind on the wrapper, sx for MUI-specific tweak
<div className="mt-4">
  <TextField
    sx={{ '& .MuiOutlinedInput-root': { borderRadius: 2 } }}
    label="Recipe title"
    {...register('title')}
  />
</div>

// Wrong — fighting two systems in one place
<TextField className="mt-4 w-full" sx={{ marginTop: '16px' }} />
```

## Do not

- Do not hardcode hex colours or use generic Tailwind palette classes where semantic tokens exist.
- Do not build standalone card pages without `PageHarness` — extend the harness if a new slot is needed.
- Do not add colours outside `src/lib/theme/tokens.ts`.
- Do not use the `style` prop for anything Tailwind or MUI can handle.
- Do not import `@emotion/react` or `@emotion/styled` directly — MUI manages Emotion internally.
- Do not create custom CSS files for component-level styles; use Tailwind utilities instead.
- Do not use `!important` overrides.
